{"lemma":"شَرِيفَةٍ","slug":"شَرِيفَةٍ","root":"ش.ر.ف","root_slug":"ش-ر-ف","root_link":"/words/roots/ش-ر-ف","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["adj"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n22169"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B4%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%81%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8D"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"noble, honored, celebrated","examples":[{"text":"كَمْ أُعَانِي مِمَّا كَتَبْتُ عَذَابًا\nوَيُعَانِي فِي شَرْقِنَا الشُّرَفَاءُ\nKam ʾuʿānī mi'm-mā katabtu ʿaḏāba'ʷ","english":"How much do I suffer as a punishment from what I have written? / And [oh, how] our honoured ones in the East are suffering!"}]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"of noble lineage"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"excellent, eminent"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From the verb شَرُفَ (šarufa, “to be noble”)."},"ipa":["/ʃa.riːf/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n22169","headword_ar":"شَرِيفٌ","root":"$rf","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"High, elevated, exalted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"eminent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, * Msb, K, TA,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in rank, condition,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"estimation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in respect of religion"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of worldly things:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) [generally meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"high-born,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"noble:"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"possessing glory, honour, dignity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nobility:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such, and having also"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ancestry:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) [using it as not implying highness, or nobility, of ancestry,] you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa $ariyfN Alyawoma","text_ar":"هُوَ شَرِيفٌ اليَوْمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is high,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"noble, to-day"},{"kind":"text","text":"], and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eano qaliylK","text_ar":"عَنْ قَلِيلٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aArifN","text_ar":"شَارِفٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one who will be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ariyf","text_ar":"شَرِيف"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"after a little while"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Fr, S, K:) the pl. [of pauc.] is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$oraAfN","text_ar":"اَشْرَافٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and [of mult.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$urafaA='u","text_ar":"شُرَفَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$arafN","text_ar":"شَرَفٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", so in the K, app. denoting that this last is one of the pls. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ryf","text_ar":"شريف"},{"kind":"text","text":", and it is said in the O that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$arafN","text_ar":"شَرَفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$urafaA='u","text_ar":"شُرَفَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but in the L it is said that it is syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ariyfN","text_ar":"شَرِيفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and hence the saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa $arafu qawomihi","text_ar":"هُوَ شَرَفُ قَوْمِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ariyf","text_ar":"شَرِيف"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of his people,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"karamuhumo","text_ar":"كَرَمُهُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kariym","text_ar":"كَرِيم"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of them;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and thus it has been expl. as used in a trad.: (TA:) [but both these assertions are probably correct; for it seems to be, agreeably with analogy, an inf. n. used as an epithet, and therefore applicable to a single person and to a pl. number, and also to two persons, and likewise to a female as well as to a male.] ―         -b2-  [By the modern Arabs, and the Turks and Persians, it is also applied, as a title of honour, to Any"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"descendant of the Prophet;"},{"kind":"text","text":"like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"say~id","text_ar":"سَيِّد"},{"kind":"text","text":". And, with the article"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al","text_ar":"ال"},{"kind":"text","text":", particularly to the descendant of the Prophet who is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The governor of Mekkeh;"},{"kind":"text","text":"now always a vassal of the Turkish Sultán.]"}],"source_refs":["TA","Fr","S","K","O","Msb"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}